<TITLE> 6 held after Chhatra League infighting at SSMC </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 9 (bdnews24.com)  Police detained six students of Sir Salimullah Medical College Tuesday after clashes between two Bangladesh Chhatra League factions over forming a new committee. Classes were suspended since morning. College principal MA Azahar said the academic council had called a meeting. Witnesses said followers of BCL leadersMohammad Jabed and Ataur Karim Arbi locked in clashes on campus at around 9:30am. The two groups were also involved in clashes Monday night. Ataur Rahman, Kotwali police sub-inspector, said they detained six BCL activists, including Jabed and Arbi, and took them to the police station "to keep the situation under control". Jabed claimed himself the president of the college unit according to the new committee formed Monday night. But Arbi and his followers were opposing the decision. bdn
